{
  "verses": [
    {
      "verse_num": 1,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Now the feast of unleavened bread drew nigh, which is called the Passover."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 2,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And the chief priests and scribes sought how they might kill him; for they feared the people."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 3,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Then entered Satan into Judas surnamed Iscariot, being of the number of the twelve."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": [
        "Satan Enters Judas"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 4,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And he went his way, and communed with the chief priests and captains, how he might betray him unto them."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 5,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And they were glad, and covenanted to give him money."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 6,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And he promised, and sought opportunity to betray him unto them in the absence of the multitude."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 7,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Then came the day of unleavened bread, when the passover must be killed."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": [
        "Preparation for Passover"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 8,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And he sent Peter and John, saying,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 9,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Where wilt thou that we prepare?",
          "speaker": "Peter and John"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 10,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And he said unto them,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 13,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And they went, and found as he had said unto them: and they made ready the passover."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 14,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And when the hour was come, he sat down, and the twelve apostles with him."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 15,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And he said unto them,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 17,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And he took the cup, and gave thanks, and said,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 19,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And he took bread, and gave thanks, and brake it, and gave unto them, saying,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": [
        "The Lord's Supper"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 20,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Likewise also the cup after supper, saying,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 23,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And they began to enquire among themselves, which of them it was that should do this thing."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 24,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And there was also a strife among them, which of them should be accounted the greatest."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": [
        "Dispute About Greatness"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 25,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And he said unto them,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 31,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "divine",
          "text": "Simon, Simon, behold, Satan hath desired to have you, that he may sift you as wheat:",
          "speaker": "The Lord"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": [
        "Jesus Predicts Peter's Denial"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 33,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Lord, I am ready to go with thee, both into prison, and to death.",
          "speaker": "Peter"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 34,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And he said,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 35,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And he said unto them,"
        },
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Nothing.",
          "speaker": "Disciples"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 36,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Then said he unto them,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 38,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Lord, behold, here are two swords.",
          "speaker": "Disciples"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And he said unto them,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 39,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And he came out, and went, as he was wont, to the mount of Olives; and his disciples also followed him."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": [
        "The Prayer in the Garden"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 40,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And when he was at the place, he said unto them,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 41,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And he was withdrawn from them about a stone's cast, and kneeled down, and prayed,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 42,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "prayer",
          "text": "Father, if thou be willing, remove this cup from me: nevertheless not my will, but thine, be done.",
          "speaker": "Jesus"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 43,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And there appeared an angel unto him from heaven, strengthening him."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 44,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And being in an agony he prayed more earnestly: and his sweat was as it were great drops of blood falling down to the ground."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 45,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And when he rose up from prayer, and was come to his disciples, he found them sleeping for sorrow,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 46,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And said unto them,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 47,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And while he yet spake, behold a multitude, and he that was called Judas, one of the twelve, went before them, and drew near unto Jesus to kiss him."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": [
        "The Betrayal"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 48,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "divine",
          "text": "Judas, betrayest thou the Son of man with a kiss?",
          "speaker": "Jesus"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 49,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Lord, shall we smite with the sword?",
          "speaker": "Disciples"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 51,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "divine",
          "text": "Suffer ye thus far.",
          "speaker": "Jesus"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And he touched his ear, and healed him."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 52,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "divine",
          "text": "Are ye come out, as against a thief, with swords and staves?",
          "speaker": "Jesus"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 54,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Then took they him, and led him, and brought him into the high priest's house. And Peter followed afar off."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": [
        "Peter's Denial of Jesus"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 57,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Woman, I know him not.",
          "speaker": "Peter"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 58,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Man, I am not.",
          "speaker": "Peter"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 60,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Man, I know not what thou sayest.",
          "speaker": "Peter"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And immediately, while he yet spake, the cock crew."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 61,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And the Lord turned, and looked upon Peter. And Peter remembered the word of the Lord, how he had said unto him, Before the cock crow, thou shalt deny me thrice."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 62,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And Peter went out, and wept bitterly."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 63,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And the men that held Jesus mocked him, and smote him."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": [
        "Jesus Mocked and Beaten"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 66,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And as soon as it was day, the elders of the people and the chief priests and the scribes came together, and led him into their council, saying,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": [
        "Jesus Before the Council"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 67,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Art thou the Christ? tell us.",
          "speaker": "Chief Priests and Elders"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And he said unto them,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 70,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Art thou then the Son of God?",
          "speaker": "Chief Priests and Elders"
        },
        {
          "type": "divine",
          "text": "Ye say that I am.",
          "speaker": "Jesus"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 71,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "What need we any further witness? for we ourselves have heard of his own mouth.",
          "speaker": "Chief Priests and Elders"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    }
  ]
}